<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<enumdef:EnumDefinitionFile xmlns:enumdef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/enumdef" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" Description="Enumeration calibrations for INFO 3.0 Language and Regionalization calibrations in the  LanguageAndRegionalizationGlobalA.caldef file. Note as clarification although this enumdef has GlobalA in it's naming convention, similar to the calibrations within the LanguageAndRegionalizationGlobalA.caldef file these enumerations do not have any Global A or Global B dependence and are used to support both either Global A or Global B. With that said, unfortunately it is too late to make a naming convention update to remove the GlobalA reference in the name to clarify that now without affecting the GM Apps software team, which are using this exact enumdef naming convention in the current MY17 and MY18 App software code releases too.">
  <EnumDefFileVersion>12</EnumDefFileVersion>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>13OCT14</Date>
    <Description>Deleted &quot;Reserved&quot; enum value names.  These are not required or allowed in caldef. </Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>14OCT14</Date>
    <Description>Removed duplicates in HMI_TEXT_LANGUAGE and COUNTRY_CODE_VARIABLES.  Renamed to COUNTRY_CODE</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>15OCT2014</Date>
    <Description>Deleted duplicate entries in KEYBOARD_LANGUAGE_ENABLE_VARIABLES</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>15OCT2014</Date>
    <Description>Deleted duplicate entries in LANGUAGE_NAVIGATION_MAP_SCRIPT</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>24OCT2014</Date>
    <Description>Deleted duplicate entries in LANGUAGE_NAVIGATION_PHONETIC_STREET_NAMES_FOR_PROMPTS</Description>
    <Author>Chris Long</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>24OCT2014</Date>
    <Description>Deleted duplicate entries in HMI_TEXT_LANGUAGE</Description>
    <Author>Chris Long</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>6/4/2015</Date>
    <Description>For the SYSTEM_LANGUAGES enumeration CAL added the new enumeration value SOUTH_AMERICAN_ENGLISH for English SA added in GIS-507 Figure 3.3.1.6 (Section: 3.3.1.4) for MY18. Within the SYSTEM_LANGUAGES enumeration CAL, updated the listing of default languages shown in the Descrition tab for the UK_ENGLISH, US_ENGLISH, RUSSIAN, DANISH, and SPANISH enumerations.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>7/30/2015</Date>
    <Description>For the SYSTEM_LANGUAGES enumeration CAL, for enumeration value 35 changed  the enumeration name from SOUTH_AMERICAN_ENGLISH to SOUTH_AFRICAN_ENGLISH to represent English SA in GIS-507 Figure 3.3.1.6 (Section: 3.3.1.4) for MY18.  Also within the SYSTEM_LANGUAGES enumeration CAL, updated the listing of default languages shown in the Descrition tab to add Isreal for US_ENGLISH enumeration and eliminate Isreal this listing for the UK_ENGLISH enumeartion.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>2/26/2016</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef, added the following additional countriies as enumeration values to the COUNTRY_CODE enumeration CAL: GEORGIA, ARMENIA, AZERBAIJAN, KYRGYZSTAN, TURKMENISTAN, TAJIKISTAN, BAHRAIN, OTHER S/E AFRICA, OTHER SOUTH AFRICA, OTHER SUB-SAHARAN AFRICA, OTHER NORTH AFRICA, SINGAPORE, AFGHANISTAN, BAHRAIN, IRAQ, and YEMEN.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>6/24/2016</Date>
    <Description>Within the LanguageAndRegionalizationGlobalA.caldef  and LanguageAndRegionalizationGlobalA.caldef LanguageAndRegionalizationGlobalA.enumdef files made the following updates: Added new TARGET_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE_ENABLE_CALIBRATIONS to allow the flexibiltiy to enable (add to the user interface display)/disable (remove from the user interface display) as needed the available system languages in the SETTINGS SYSTEM LANGUAGE selection menu instead of tying the display of the available system languages to the COUNTRY_CODE calibration as was being done previously. Renamed the SYSTEM_LANGUAGE calibration to DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE and updated the description of this calibration to clarify the intended purposes of this calibration. Also, updated the enumeration value names and values for each of these enumeration to correspond to the Software Mapping (Hexadecimal Converted) number shown in the GIS-547 to make it easier to follow corresponding enumeration references in relation to the GIS-547. Added on to the description shown for the COUNTRY_CODE calibration to clarify that this calibration is also being used as referenced in GIS-331 Wifi Calibration Specification for determining the regulatory wifi power variation settings to use for the wifi chip that shall be dynamically determined and set based on the value (country value) set for this calibration. Also added additonal COUNTRY_CODE enumeration values that needed to be added. Deleted the following three calibrations that were confirmed by Thiep Nguyen not to be needed for NAV: 1.) LANGUAGE_NAVIGATION_MAP_SCRIPT, 2.) LANGUAGE_NAVIGATION_PHONETIC_STREET_NAMES_FOR_PROMPTS, and 3.) LANGUAGE_NAVIGATION_PHONETIC_POINTS_OF_INTEREST. Deleted the following two calibrations: 1.) LANGUAGE_SPEECH_VOICE_RECOGNITION and 2.) TEXT_TO_SPEECH_MANEUVER_PROMPTS_AND_MESSAGE_READBACK that were confirmed by Greg Lindemann not to be needed for voice recognition/speech recongniton. Deleted the KEYBOARD_LANGUAGES calibration  (along with the associated KEYBOARD_LANGUAGE_ENABLE_VARIABLES enumeration calibration) confirmed by team (Greg Frietag, Paul Hollenbeck, and Scott Griesmann) not to be needed. Also, deleted the HMI_TEXT_LANGUAGE calibration that was confirmed not to be needed with the use of the DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE calibration that has the same function. Also, deleted the following three calibrations 1.) DATE_FORMAT_DISPLAYED_VARIABLES, 2.) DATE_FORMAT_SEPERATOR_VARIABLES, and 3.) GRAPHICS_ANIMATION_THEMES_VAIRABLES since these calibrations were confirmed by Cody Hansen not be needed. Note these calibrations are not needed because the date format displayed and date format separator are automatically determined by the language setting selected, and the GRAPHICS_ANIMATION_THEMES_VAIRABLES calibration is not needed since the GMBrand calibration is already being used for the purpose of what this calibration was going to be used for. </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>7/1/2016</Date>
    <Description>Changed the name of the LanguageAndRegionalizationGlobalA.enumdef file to LanguageAndRegionalization.enumdef for this enumdef file to be consistent with the specific naming convention being used starting in the initial MY19 CAL Database release to not have any reference to GlobalA or GlobalB in the caldef/enumdef naming convention if calibrations contained in a caldef/enumdef file are not GlobalA or GlobalB specific.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>11/7/2016</Date>
    <Description>Added the country GAZA (shown in the country support list of GIS-547) to the country enumeration list for the COUNTRY_CODE calibration.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>11/21/2016</Date>
    <Description> Changed the names of both the LanguageAndRegionalization caldef/enumdef files back to LanguageAndRegionalizationGlobalA. The name of these caldef/enumdef files were changed initially to help make it clearer that the calibrations within these caldef/enumdef files are not Global A specific calibrations, and these calibrations are intended to be used for both Global A and B. However, a naming convention change to these caldef/enumdef files would cause the GM Apps team to support a different software branch for MY19 than what was done for MY17 and MY18, which the GM Apps team confirmed could not be supported long term. </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>6/13/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the LanguageAndRegionalizationGlobalA.enumdef file added four additonal enumerations values ( 1. HONG_KONG, 2. INDONESIA, 3. MALAYSIA, and 4. NO MAX TRANSMIT POWER REQUIREMENT) to the COUNTRY_CODE enumeration calibration and included a description for the COUNTRY_CODE enumerations that did not have a description previously.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>1/12/2018</Date>
    <Description>Within the LanguageAndRegionalizationGlobalA.enumdef file, added the following 51 additional countries needed per GIS-547 and pertient vehicle PPCs to the COUNTRY_CODE calibration enumeration list: 1.) BERMUDA, 2,) ANTIGUA, 3.) BARBUDA, 4.) HAITI, 5.) JAMAICA, 6.) REPUBLIC OF TRINIDAD AND TOBAGO, 7.) TURKS AND CAICOS ISLAND, 8.) BELIZE, 9.) HONDURAS, 10.) NICARAGUA, 11.) LIBYA, 12.) MOROCCO, 13.) TUNISIA, 14.) BENIN, 15.) CAPE VERDE ISLANDS, 16.) BURUNDI, 17.) BURKINA FASO, 18.) CAMEROON, 19.) CHAD, 20.) EQUATORIAL GUINEA, 21.) ERITREA, 22.) GABON, 23.) GUINEA, 24.) GUINEA BISSAU, 25.) MADAGASCAR, 26.) MALI, 27.) TOGO, 28.) RWANDA, 29.) GAMBIA, 30.) ANGOLA, 31.) CENTRAL AFRICA, 32.) COMORO ISLANDS, 33.) DEMOCRATIC REPUBLIC OF THE CONGO, 34.) DJIBOUTI, 35.) ETHIOPIA, 36.) GHANA, 37.) NIGER, 38.) NIGERIA, 39.) SENEGAL, 40.) SIERRA_LEONE, 41.) SOMALIA, 42.) ST LUCIA, 43.) SURINAM, 44.) FIJI, 45.) MYANMAR, 46.) CAMBODIA, 47.) LAOS, 48.) TAHITI, 49.) NEW CALEDONIA, 50.) BRUNEI, and 51.) BARBADOS. </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
  <EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>12</Version>
    <Date>09/18/2018</Date>
    <Description>Added additional countries (Algeria, Liberia, and Northen Mariana Island) not previously listed in the COUNTY_CODE enumeration list in LanguageandRegionalization.enumdef </Description>
    <Author>Ibnul Khan</Author>
  </EnumDefFileChangeRecord>
