  <EnumDefinition Description="Default language enumeration list. Used to set the initial default system language that is available in the SETTINGS SYSTEM LANGUAGE selection menu. The DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE shall be checked to confirm it is one of the available system languages enabled at a given time by the TARGET_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE_ENABLE_CALIBRATIONS. If at any time the value set for the DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE calibration is not one of the available system languages enabled by the TARGET_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE_ENABLE_CALIBRATIONS, the DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE calibration shall be set to a fail safe value based on the value the REGION calibration is set to at that time. For the purpose of referencing the REGION calibration to determine the fail safe value to set the DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE calibration if the REGION calibration is set to any of the following four REGION enumeration calibration values of 1.) EUROPE, 2.) AFRICA, 3.) AUSTRALIA, or 4.) INDIA, the DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE calibration shall be set to a fail safe default system language of ENGLISH_UK. Otherwise if the REGION calibration is not set to any one of these four Region enumeration calibration values, the DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE calibration shall be set to a fail safe default system language of ENGLISH_US." Name="DEFAULT_SYSTEM_LANGUAGE">
    <EnumID>_sJrvYLEKEeO_VpIpRoy4MQ</EnumID>
    <EnumDefinitionVersion>4</EnumDefinitionVersion>
    <EnumValueDefinition Description="From GIS-547: Target Language = English; Locale = en-US" Name="ENGLISH_US">
      <Value>0</Value>
    </EnumValueDefinition>
